## рҹ”¬ What is UniversalMind?

UniversalMind is a rigorous experimental platform for studying **emergent coordination in recursive self-improving multi-agent systems**. It extends the [Godelion](https://github.com/NullLabTests/godelion) evolutionary self-improvement paradigm into a multi-agent context, enabling empirical testing of a fundamental question:

> **Do recursive self-improving multi-agent systems converge toward globally coordinated behavior that cannot be explained by local rules alone?**

### Primary Research Hypothesis

The system is designed to test two competing hypotheses:

| Hypothesis | Prediction |
|---|---|
| **H1 вҖ” Local Reducibility** | All coordination is reducible to local interaction + communication. Cross-agent behavioral coupling is fully explained by the information channel bandwidth. |
| **H2 вҖ” Emergent Unity** | Evolution produces emergent global structure resembling a unified optimization process. Coordination exceeds what communication bandwidth alone can explain, implying shared latent structure. |

**You are not allowed to assume H2. The system must attempt to falsify it.**

### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **рҹ§¬ Darwinian Evolution** | Agent populations evolve through selection, mutation, and crossover with fitness-based pressure |
| **рҹ”„ Recursive Self-Improvement** | Mutation strategies, selection pressures, and evaluation heuristics themselves evolve (meta-RSI) |
| **рҹӨқ Multi-Agent Universe** | 5вҖ“50 agents in a partially observable grid world with communication channels |
| **рҹ’¬ Communication Systems** | Vector, discrete symbolic, and attention-based message routing with learnable protocols |
| **рҹ“Ҡ Rigorous Metrics** | Mutual information, synchronization index, communication entropy, coordination scores, emergence indicators, phase transition detection |
| **рҹ§Ә Falsifiable Design** | Every metric is designed to test whether coordination exceeds communication-bounded predictions |
| **рҹ”Ғ Meta-Evolution** | Not just agents, but mutation strategies and evolutionary parameters themselves undergo selection |
| **рҹ“Ҳ Full Visualization** | Fitness curves, coordination heatmaps, communication entropy plots, phase transition detection |
| **рҹ”җ Reproducible** | Deterministic seeding, configuration-driven experiments, full audit trail |
| **рҹ–ҘпёҸ Local-First** | Pure Python/NumPy вҖ” no external APIs, no Docker requirement. Runs on any machine. |

